inn1.comm: misdirected, no swing first-up, and that zips down leg
outside off, and nips off the seam. Left alone
angled down the leg side again, and flicked to midwicket
full length, outside off, driven to point with an open face
a slashing square drive, straight to third man who fields on one knee. The first attacking shot of the day
full length, outside off stump, fizzes through to the keeper
streaky, but safe in the end. McCullum comes forward in a checked drive that loops over the bowler's head and all the way to the fence. A fraction early on the stroke, but well timed all the same
pitches leg and angles across, tucked to midwicket for a single
perfect line and length, and from 16000 miles away I swear there was a nick. But closer to the action, no-one is moved, and a dot-ball ensues
outside off, back of a length, defended into the covers
banged in, good short ball and the perfect response as McCullum hurtles down the track in premeditated fashion.

massive breakthrough and that's good aggression from Anderson. Another short ball, angling in and cramping McCullum as he attempted to cut his way out of trouble. Alastair Cook at slip claims a simple looped chance. England are up and running
good length and tight line, defended out to point and that's the end of a great first over
outside off, angling into the left-hander, defended. Ryder bides his time after his partner's loss
another firm push off a good length, but fielded with a flourish in the covers
outside off and nibbling away from a limp back-foot prod. Good seam position, and Ryder is beaten
dead-batted into space on the leg-side, and they take a quick single
outside off, zipping through to the keeper. Tidy lines from England's seamers
slipping down leg and a massive appeal as Mustard claims the catch, but that clipped the thigh-pad on the way through. No reaction from Sidebottom, nor the umpire
drawn forward, defended to cover
outside off again, angling across the left-hander, left alone
driven firmly to cover, but fielded with ease
that's a brilliant piece of timing, nothing more than a dismissive flick off a good length, but it's carried ten rows back! Ryder has serious power in his strokes ...
good response, a little bit quicker and Ryder can't time his second attempt. The ball bobbles into the slips
another swish and a miss. The end of a good over with a solitary sizeable blemish
tucked into the leg-side, and a scampered single
thrashed through the off side, just a fraction too much width, but hit on the up, and past the diving Collingwood at point
angled down the leg-side, hits the pad
stands tall and pushes out to point where Collingwood stoops to field
picks the gap, jogged single to the off side
angled bat, defended into the gully region. Another over ticks by
driven firmly into the covers
another thrashed drive, but wide mid-off fields easily enough
raps the pads from wide of the crease. How was shaping to clip through the leg side. Yelped appeal
slower ball, just rolled his fingers at the point of delivery. Scudded through to the keeper
short and driven backward of point with immense timing, it's a short boundary down there as well
good riposte, extra oomph behind the ball, and through to the keeper
driven on the up, fielded in the covers
a fraction short, tucked neatly off the hip, down to square leg
drawn forward in an angled defensive block
a leg-stump half-volley, and Ryder misses out with a bit of a gimme. Instead his clip rolls tamely to deep midwicket. The scoreboard keeps moving though
flicked square again. Fielded on the edge of the circle
pitches on leg, and steered to midwicket. Another decent over
square-driven again, Collingwood is being kept busy at point
outside off stump, too wide for Ryder to time his drive properly. Mid-off fields
lovely bowling, zipping past an expansive drive
angled in from outside off, defended on the back foot. Good bowling
climbing off a good length, towards the thigh pad. Nudged into space at square leg
bouncer, and a good one. Ryder tucks his head inside the line, and that's the end of the over
that's a fantastic strike, straight through the line and all along the ground to the long-off boundary
defended on the walk with the straightest of straight bats
on the pads and worked into space in front of square
slower ball, pushed to cover
much wider delivery, and swatted off the toe-end to point. Missed opportunity
full-length, on the pads and Ryder can't work it away
driven into space at extra cover
back of a length, defended into the covers. Tight lines once again
thrashed into the covers again, but can't beat the infield
full-length, no room to free the arms, cover picks up a bottom-handed drive
excellent line and length in this over so far, defended on off stump
streaky shot, that was an lbw candidate as he wafted across the line of a full-length ball. But he got enough bat on it
pushed off a thickish edge square on the off side
firmer push on the walk to extra cover
clipped to deepish midwicket, worked neatly off the pads

How looks to drive through extra cover, the ball squirts off a thick edge and scoots to the left of Collingwood at backward point who takes a good, low catch ... it wasn't going hard but it was dying on him
outside off, cutting back in slightly but wide enough for him to leave with ease
straighter and very carefully watched and blocked

the sucker punch ... short, Ryder pulls and it goes straight down the throat of the man out in the deep five yards behind square. Mascarenhas hardly has to move and he turns and shows the ball to spectators who have been giving him some verbals
slight short outside off, he goes down on his haunches and lets it pass
clipped off his toes to deep backward square leg
little more than a firm push between the bowler and mid-on, well timed and it goes almost all the way to the rope
a tip and run to short extra cover, Taylor is quick and although Shah hits with a diving underarm throw, he's easily home
solid block to a straight one
gentle drive to wide mid-on
swinging in, well played with bat and pad together, pushed back to Broad who drops a hand to field
super ball, seaming away from a defensive poke and beating the outside edge
fuller, Styris back to defend
pushed firmly to extra cover, Styris is interested but his colleague yells "wait, wait,wait" ... and so wait he does
crisp drive to mid-off
cut from close to the body, it goes at catchable height inches to the left of Cook in the gully
blocked with a shuffle
pushed square on the off side with a very open face
good length outside off, no shot
caution as they look to rebuild, no shot to a widish one
shoulders arms again
into his pads and turned from the crease behind square on the leg side
Broad swinging the ball in, Taylor well forward, bat and pad as one, pushed into the off side
eased off his pads to deep midwicket, not quite timed and deep square leg able to cut it off without too much haste
placed to the right of mid-off and as the fielder has to tumble to stop it, there's an easy single

short, he pulls from outside off and Mascarenhas at shortish midwicket takes a really good catch above his head. It was slightly too short for the pull and that's why he couldn't get on top of it and ended up playing more of a tennis swat
lazily flicked to midwicket
patted into the off side
a rich cover drive off one knee, it looked superb but had no timing and extra cover's hands are not exactly stung by the power
a more low-key pat to cover
back onto his stumps and pushed to midwicket
fractionally short, cut to Collingwood at backward point
pushed to cover to complete a maiden from Broad
half forward and blocked
defensive poke into the off side
gentle prod to mid-off, he ducks with good agility for a big man
banged in at 81mph,
steps back and cuts hard to cover
turned past a diving midwicket  ... the very man just moved!
angled across the right hander who leaves
back and defended to mid-on from deep in the crease
again played with minimal footwork from the crease
wider and fuller, he comes forward but the drive has little power
driven and he finally finds a gap between cover and extra cover, Collingwood charges after it, slides, and keeps them down to two
pushed back to Sidebottom who fields,scowls and then heads off into the deep
flicked into the leg side
driven on the bounce to mid-off
pushed into the leg side, short midwicket in very quickly and the ball bounces kindly so he doesn't even have to bend
worked to deep midwicket
dribbled into the off side
paddled into the leg side, placed into space
he shuffles to the off and defends to leg
patted into the leg side
clipped into the deep out in the midwicket region, Taylor wanted to come back for what would have been a risky third but  Fulton was having none of it
a thick edge to backward point
turned to leg, as his natural shuffle to the off means he will always favour, Fulton has to hurl himself full length to beat a shy at the stumps which in the event misses by a long way
very wide and full, he bottom ends the ball into the ground as he looks to cover drive and the ball apologetically dribbles away
bang on the button again, defended
flicked to deep backward square leg - 84mph
blocked from the crease, again not much footwork but he's got a good eye
Fulton content to take his time to get going
pushed back to the right of Broad who reacts quickly and fields well
poked rather half-heartedly to mid-off
good start from the skipper, pushed to leg
short and Taylor quick to spot that, he pulls high over midwicket but Broad in the deep fields on the sliding run helped by a kind bounce
patted back to the bowler
stands tall and pushed to cover
cuts, misses, and Mustard, standing up, takes and yelps in frustration as the ball sneaks past the edge
straight through a large gap between bat and pad - his footwork has been minimal throughout -  and the off stump is sent flying
drifts to leg and helped round the corner
firm push to point
languid push from a length to deepish mid-off
the previous ball was a sighter ... Oram saw he was deep and took the pace of pretty much the same shot and called for the single. Mascarenhas picked up and threw but Oram was always home
midwicket fields a ball which has little pace
short and outside off at 82mph, Taylor thinks about the pull but whips his bat out of the way as the ball climbs on him
stands tall and plays a very loose back-foot drive with no footwork, gets a thin inside edge and Mustard has no chance
pushed on the walk to extra cover
marooned in the crease, he shuffles to the off and is hit right in front ... Sidebottom roars a confident appeal but the umpire is having none of it
back and turned to leg, again no footwork
pushed back to Sidebottom who shapes to hurl the ball back at the batsman but fumbles it and has to make do with a scowl
outside off and defended, Sidebottom, clearly livid at the earlier decision, stands muttering to nobody in particular
a gentle 67mph loosener  flicked to midwicket
angled in, dropped into the leg side and a scurried single
straight, angled across and Mustard takes
driven to mid-off
driven to the right of Broad, he dives and makes a good stop, again the ball bounced kindly into his hands
very solid forward defensive push to cover
worked into the leg side
he pushes from the crease and gets a thick edge which dribbles to point
firm checked drive, short extra cover slides in on his knees to prevent the run
short, he sways back out of the way, pivoting from the knees
good shorter ball, chest high and Oram has to hurry as he goes back but he gets over the ball, dropping it safely at his feet
half forward, he drives to mid-off
forward and pushed back to the bowler
straight and defended
poor fielding, Broad too deep and that allows the single, and then he throws at the stumps with the batsman well home, and the deflection allows an overthrow
pushed to Anderson at mid-on, he is in quickly and his underarm throw just misses ... that would have been close but Taylor would have made it
driven to Anderson who has retreated to long-off
the storm after the lull ... down on one knee and sweep-pulled ten rows back into banks of empty blue seats. A lovely shot but where on earth did the aggression come from!
worked into space on the off side
straight and defended. "Oh yes, Colly," comes from behind the stumps
Taylor back in his shell after that big blow
tip and run to Anderson at mid-on who drops to his knees but doesn't bother throwing at the stumps
firm clip round his leading leg to mid-on
plays to the same man, Sidebottom slightly slow to react and that allows the single
driven to mid-off who is in quickly
Oram gets into the mood with a well-timed straight drive over long-on. Effortless and sweet
from brutal to delicate, he opens the face and runs it to third man
mid-on fields, and as we suspected he has come in a yard or so an
into the off side, Oram starts, stops and then starts again, Wright throws at the bowler's end and just misses ... he would have been OK
driven to long-on where Broad fields
pushed to leg
pulled just in front of midwicket whose dive is in vain

oh dear ... salt in the wound. First the six is discounted and three balls later Taylor misses a straight one and is given lbw. He was a long way forward but it wasn't high.  In normal circumstances that would be okay, but given what has already happened this over, it's bound to be a discussion point ...
full, Vettori plays a half volley to mid-on
outside off, angled across
dropped ... checked drive clips the fingers of the outstretched hands of Anderson and it carries on for four
tidy line and length to start, bustles through to the keeper
tight line, and beats Oram's wafted pull
driven into the covers
good bowling from Wright, pitches middle, angling towards off, defended to raucous acclaim from Mustard behind the stumps
chipped in the air through midwicket, but safe
short, and pulled flat behind square, where Anderson fields well on the slide at fine leg. Not a bad first over
short, and clobbered through midwicket. Top biffing
slower ball, clipped - in the air - huge shouts of "caaaaaatch" from Mustard but it lands just short
"that's good, Colly, that's good ..." and it is
hint of width, Vettori misses an attempted glide to third man
the same again, a dab and a miss. Good take by Mustard
tucked to midwicket
stands tall and drives back down the ground, but with no great timing
more white noise from Mustard, to another nondescript delivery
wide, and dabbed down to third man, good contact this time
width again, and driven out to point
firm push back to the bowler, who parries in his followthrough and Bell at mid-on tidies up
a fraction too much width, and that's flashed hard up and over backward point
slower ball, emerges as a rank full toss, and it's merely placed down the ground through long-off
much better slower ball, a genuine offcutter this time, and third man tidies up
another offcutter, and a hopeless misfield at point by Bell gifts an extra run
slightly back of a length, nurdled to third man
driven, in the air, to mid-off
full-length outswinger to the left-hander, Vettori watches it onto the middle of his bat, and that's a useful over of accumulation
another slower ball, clipped behind square
pushed firmly into the deep cover region, useful stand now forming
lovely firm strike, as straight as can possibly be, but Broad fields superbly at full-stretch on the boundary's edge
driven again, through mid-on this time, and Broad fields with less drama
tucked off the hip, straight to midwicket
defended out to point, a bit of a scramble for the non-striker, who'd backed up too far, but he's safe
good length to start things off. Defended to point
leg-stump half-volley, and that's sweetly threaded through midwicket. Lovely timing
back outside off stump, and nudged down to the boundary's edge at third man
shorter, and half-pulled into space at midwicket
yorker, and a good one, swinging from middle to off stump, and pushed back to the bowler
wider outside off, angling away, Vettori attempts to run it past third man but point intercepts
calm push into the gap at midwicket
an energetic thump over cover. Shouts of "catch" but never close to a fielder. Good strike
back on a tidy line and length, defended
thumped through the covers again, but Mascarenhas has dropped back and cuts off the boundary
driven into the covers again
a hint of width to work with, and that's under-edged to third man, where Sidebottom sweeps round to field
full-length outswinger, pushed to cover
wide of off stump, steered with an open face to gully
nudged off middle stump to midwicket
turned fine, looking for two and getting them
straying onto leg stump, turned backward of square
full length, looping onto the pads, and clipped to midwicket to bring up the fifty partnership
open-faced glide to point
a measured push down to long-off, no fireworks just yet ...
if he'd hit, that was curtains. Pushed straight to Wright at mid-off, who misses with an underarm shy ... close
clipped to midwicket
floated into the blockhole, dug out down to long-off
another measured push to long-off. Tight over
outswinger, beats an attempted steer, well taken by Mustard
open-faced glide to third man. New Zealand are happy to deal in singles for the moment
offcutter, tucked to midwicket
driven in the air, but not dangerously so. Picked up at deep cover
yorker, and a good one. Hastily dug out
low full toss, chip-driven to mid-on
yorker, dug out into the off side
swung over wide midwicket, he stepped to leg and gave himself room to heave that
once more he steps to leg but this time the bowler fires one in outside off, vettori jabs down and squeezes the ball to third man, good adjustment
firm drive straight down the ground, between the men in the deep and that allows them a second
half volley cracked to long-off
full toss thumped to bell at wide midwicket, they run the single to bell whose throw is fired in at Mustard's feet and it thwacks Vettori as he runs past the stumps
full at 76mph, turned to midwicket where there is now a large gap with the man out in the deep
he steps to leg and heaves inches past the outstretched hand of mid-on who is at full stretch
as he now does every ball, Vettori steps to the leg and gives himself room, but this time he pulls the ball straight to Shah at deep midwicket
a big step forward and blocked
steered to point
very watchful start by Mills, patted into the off side
full, driven to long on, to bring up his fifty ... the ninth time he has passed that score in an ODI.
deliberately run down to third man to get Oram back on strike
very wide and very full, a really good take by Mustard as it bounced on the edge of the crease and a foot in front of him
clipped to long-off
very correct and tight forward defensive shot
tip and run into the off side, hesitation between the two and the throw is not good enough or fast enough. Even if he had hit directly Oram would have made it
square drive to Shah at deep cover
full toss smacked back to Collingwood who dives to his right to make a really sharp stop. It hurt him for sure and he holds his knee and grimaces ...
driven on the half volley to long-on
hit high and straight, but too much elevation and it plugs as it hits the turf ten yards in from the boundary ... quite safe as the straight fielders were both in on the single
straight drive skews off an inside edge to long leg
textbook straight drive all along the ground, Anderson slides and stops from long-off
wristy swish off his pads to deep midwicket
wide, driven to Pietersen at extra cover who fumbles
slashed drive to deep cover, a safe shot and he hit that well
wide and full, driven to wide long-on and a no-ball to add to Mascarenhas' woes. he has caught well but this is not his day, and now he has a free hit off him
what a shot!  Mascarenhas went wide and full, and Oram squeezed the ball over cover for six ... a long way back and a stroke of real class
cut hard to deep cover, he middled that
pushed to leg
hammered off the back foot to long-on
pushed with an open face into the off side
slower ball -  73mph - driven through backward point's dive ... he half stopped in fairness to him
half volley driven to extra cover but he was not able to place it
early on the pull as Broad drops to 74mph, and the ball dribbles to the right of midwicket

short, Mills takes the bait and hooks, gets a big top edge and Cook comes in from the deep-midwicket boundary and has to make a late adjustment and dive forward to hold the ball inches above the turf. In this breeze that must have been swirling around and he did well
turned off his pads to long leg to keep the strike
dug out to cover for a strolled single
clipped off his toes to backward square leg
yorker, driven hard into the ground, Sidebottom jabs out his left hand and it sticks
low full toss driven to long-on
full and straight, Hitchcock can do no more than push it into the off side
another good ball which a No.10 can do little but block
low full toss, he opens the face and pushes to deep cover
squeezed into the covers
this time he finds the gap between cover fielders and scampers the single
short and a top-edge hook carries with the wind for six ... the man behind square was in so he was left vainly searching the skies over his shoulder as he turned to try to catch it
fuller and heaved over midwicket into the stands, two in two
wider and fuller, Oram settles for the steer to deep cover to keep the strike
inswinging full toss thumped to long-on
takes two strides to leg, the ball follows him and he drives to long-on
good length, Oram swings but takes pitch and ball together and that takes the power out of the shot ... a single to long-on
full and straight again ... driven to long-on
Oram gives him the charge and gets thwacked by a waist-high full toss

another full toss, Oram thumps that over Bell at wide mid-on, it seems for all the world to be falling beyond him but he turns, runs and dives full length to take a brilliant catch as the ball drops over his shoulder
he shimmies to the off, Sidebottom follows and the ball thuds off his pads into the leg side ... you could see all three stumps plus some space when he played that
two big steps and a rasping drive well stopped by extra cover

a swish, more in hope than expectation, a thin edge into the pads and into the on side, had midwicket's throw hit at the non-striker's end then he would have been short, as it was extra cover had to make a good stop to prevent four overthrows
dribbled behind on the off side
drive of a sort to mid-on, he sets off but is rightly sent back
full toss, gets an inside edge and his scouring of the outfield shows he has no idea where it has gone ... long leg fields
a super shot to end the innings, he plants his feet and thumps the ball over the extra-cover boundary

inn2.comm: good grief, chaos already. Cook defends to short cover, Mustard is three-quarters of the way down the pitch and sent back, and the shy hits straightaway ... but he's just home
pushed into the leg-side, and no panic this time
full length, driven down to mid-on
width outside off stump, Too much width as it turns out
outside off stump and left alone with a flourish
a swish and a miss. That was quite wide too, but Cook all but edged it
good delivery, seaming back into the left-hander, who edges with soft hands, just short of second slip
short and wide, and Mustard loves that. Clobbered through the covers, leaning back for extra effect
tighter line but same approach. Mustard flings the bat at it, and under-edges into the crease
lovely shot, just rides the bounce because he's cramped for room, and picks his spot behind square on the off side. He's not just a biffer, he can time it too
tighter line, and respectfully defended, out to point
sliding down leg, tucked fine
angled into the left-hander, defended
defended, after all that fuss
nudged down to the gully region
short, and a spiralling top-edge flies all the way over the keeper's head for six! Mustard rumbles on in his unique fashion
fuller, straighter, defended with a vertical blade
outside off, nurdled to point with a curl of the wrists

tapped into the covers, and Vettori pings down the stumps with Mustard nowhere near the frame! That's England's seventh run-out in this series. Their fielders didn't hit the stumps once, now New Zealand have made direct hits twice in two attempts ...
short, and swung away dismissively over midwicket - top strike, he knew what was coming. That's a good way to mark your arrival
attempted back-foot drive, not quite middled
short of a length, and pushed comfortably into the gap. There's definitely a run on offer there
on the pads, angled in from round the wicket, and that's sweetly timed through midwicket. Slows up near the ropes, but it's a short boundary
full length, on off stump. Defended
big stride, firm block, picked up at cover
drifting onto the pads, and clipped away to square leg
tucked neatly off the toes, and picked up just inside the rope - perhaps the rain has slowed the outfield a touch
zips through outside off stump
defended with a hasty late adjustment, in front of middle and off
pushed into the gap in the covers, and a good solid call for once
wicket-to-wicket delivery, defended in front of off  stump
round the wicket, angling into the left-hander, defended on off stump
doesn't get up, left alone
a hint of a shimmy down the pitch, but in the end just nudged to mid-on
tidy line, angling towards off stump, pushed out to point
width, and cut firmly to point
a maiden over - Oram's having a good day. Cook tries to work the gap in the covers, but can't beat the field
outside off and left alone
two steps down the track, and clipped to leg, but a fine dive at square leg from Fulton prevents the run
onto the back foot, and pushed into the covers. The runs have dried up, much like the rain
worked to point, ten dot balls in a row now
good full-length delivery, met with a straight bat. Another dot ball
two maidens in a row. Nothing more than good lengths and tight lines, and the cover fielders have done the rest
a packed off-side field, and there's no piercing it at present
that was pure pressure - nothing more, nothing less. A length ball, smeared in front of square on the leg side, and straight to the solitary fielder at mid-on. England are wobbling
nurdled into the leg side, not entirely convincingly, but he's off the mark
two steps down the wicket again, and worked to leg
big stride, and picked up at mid-on
looking to work through the leg-side, but finds a thick outside-edge to third man instead. They all count
great delivery, probing the off stump, and Pietersen draws his bat inside the line at the last minute
banged in and pushed out to point
that's the Pietersen of old - a full stride, big reach, and thumped along the ground to long-off
attempting the same shot, but inside-edges onto his pads. Looks like he's reaching for the ball
left alone outside off
big stride again, and defended into the covers
pushed defensively into the off side
super cover drive on the up, textbook and all that
pushed into the covers
completely undone by the slower ball, he takes a step down the pitch and misses ... and ends up looking utterly bemused
played off the back foot into the covers
angled behind square on the off, Pietersen quick to call for the single - he was heading to the danger end - even if Bell was less certain
firm drive to extra cover
back of a length, defended off the back foot
slightly short, one step from Bell and swatted over wide mid-on for a one-bounce four, quite safe with the men inside the circle and there's nobody back there
off drive, but at the man and hit too firmly for the single
and again, this time he takes two big steps and flicks the ball over mid-on, using his feet to take it on the half volley and ease it over the infield
worked square on the leg side
he comes down the track, the bowler responds with a slower ball and Bell steers defensively into the off side
a loud shout from bowler and keeper as the ball skids through a defensive poke, but there was an inside edge and a single results into the leg side
firm block to mid-on
he works the ball from outside off stump to mid-on and immediately takes on the fielder ... easily home and the throw is wild as well
straight half volley driven to mid-on
patted into the off side
mistimed drive from wide of the crease
a typical Pietersen shuffle to meet the ball, well directed and he has to settle for a defensive push to cover
drives on the up from outside off stump, gets a thick edge and the ball scurries into the midwicket area
slower ball, he waits and then thumps it to mid-on who returns the ball with interest and hits the stumps behind Pietersen
another slower ball, turned to midwicket and Bell has to hurl himself to try to beat Styris' throw at the batsman's end ... but he wasn't even in the frame had it hit
pushed a few yards into the off side
fairly hard drive but to mid-off
little more than a chip on the rise, he shaped to hit over mid-on but it clears mid-off with more than a sniff of edge
pressed into the covers and loud calls of "no" from both ends
worked to midwicket where Taylor is quickly in
too much width, he leans back and larrups that through the covers, a perfect height for that stroke
plopped towards backward point, Bell starts as if looking for the single but is firmly sent back
flowery and upright cover drive, well stopped by a diving How
pushed from outside off  - almost all from the wrists - and they take on mid-on but Mills misfields and falls over as well to add to the rather comedy moment
yorker, well dug out, the ball bounces and spins viciously back into the bowler's-end stumps to loud cheers
hard drive to mid-off and a good run
left alone outside off stump
inside-out drive into the off side
good start, on the spot and blocked
back and driven to mid-off
69mph ... that's more like it ... driven to mid-off but extra cover dives and tips it past his team-mate
and back to 81mph. No way ... pushed to mid-off
punched to mid-on who is quite deep
gives himself room and drives but right to extra cover
tip and run to mid-on ... they're taking him on, almost daring him. What price a run-out soon?
firm drive from wide of the crease to extra cover
slashing drive, he opens the face to steer the ball between point and cover
more orthodox drive to cover
slower and slightly shorter, he waits and runs the ball off the face of the bat to third man
driven on the half volley, not timed but very straight, deepish mid-off and mid-on converge to field
short, bottom edge into his stomach and down to long leg
tight bowling and defended into the off
short and on leg stump, Bell swivels and helps that on its way, too fine for the man on the 45 to have any chance
inside edge as he drives, Pietersen starts off for the run and has to scoot back as midwicket fields and throws
firm drive, a tumbling stop by extra cover
back and flicked off his legs square on the leg side, deep midwicket scuttles round to field
good start, on a length and on the stumps, solidly defended
again defended, albeit with a flick to leg
back, he gets turned square on as he blocks
tossed up at 50mph and Pietersen treats with great respect
he looks to leave and then at the last second attempts a cut and, unsurprisingly,  misses
punched into the off side
lovely cover drive, through the gap in the covers and it purrs across the turf
a single into the covers and his 15th score of fifty comes up ...only one of those has been converted into a hundred though
poked into the off side
a big backlift but a dead bat
big off drive but an even bigger inside edge and the ball dribbles to square leg
short ... well, a rank long hop ... pulled with power to deep midwicket
short but he gets away with it as the cut is thumped into the ground which takes all the power off it
flatter and faster, defended
fired in, he goes back and defends
tossed up, crisply driven to a diving extra cover
he steps back and waits, then swishes the ball to deep midwicket
cut from slightly too close to him, no power or placement and it scoots to short third man
defended into the off side
again they take on the fielder - Vettori at mid-off - and had the throw hit then bell was kippered
pushed into the leg side and another tight run
that one slipped ... well taken very wide of the off stump, way outside the tram lines
more air, cracked hard but at extra cover
back and cuts into the covers
punched into the off side
cut to point
drifting down the leg side, but no contact
quick feet, and defended in the end, with a gaping hole between bat and pad. Deceived in flight
rotates the strike well with a dab into space on the off side
defended to point
pushed into the covers
bouncer, a good one too, surprises Pietersen as he sways inside the line
flogged out to deep cover with a big stride and bigger followthrough. Still not quite timing it today though
hurried onto the middle of the pad
pushed into space in the covers
defended back down the pitch, and Pietersen is sent sprawling for the crease
defended
defended again. Pietersen bides his time
pushed out to point
opens the face and runs down to third man
big stride, and turned to midwicket
attempts to work into the leg side, but no contact
defended again. Probing stuff
driven into the covers, and just falls short of a diving Styris at short cover
turned to leg
driven out to cover
short, and flogged through the leg side. That was a rank long-hop, to be honest, and Pietersen - in or out of form - doesn't miss those
that might be the cataylst that KP has needed. This one is belted through the covers at a severe rate of knots ... and the rain gets heavier
Pietersen is in a serious hurry now. Another full stride and a thumping straight drive. England are consolidating their position now
looped onto leg stump, tucked out to square leg
pushed out to point
attempted drive off the back foot, but not properly connected
drawn forward in the flight and defended slightly uneasily into the covers
looking to work to leg, but his ambitions are stifled by some teasing flight
short, and shovelled over the leg side. A very elegant shovel too ...
trying to work to leg again, but no proper contact
swings across the line, but it lands one-bounce in front of deep midwicket
back and across, aiming to work through midwicket
pushed out to point off the back foot
the end of another over, and England are ... dare one say it ... in control
another big stride, and a measured push into the leg side
stretches forward and pushed to mid-off
makes room to flog through the off side, and times the ball well. The cover sweeper tidies up well
another single into the leg-side. England are beginning to milk Vettori effectively now
more good running, nothing more than a deflection into the leg-side, but an easy single
the arm-ball to finish the over, but still another run. New Zealand need wickets
another direct hit, but this time Bell was safely in his crease. They rarely miss
stands tall at the crease and batters the ball back down the ground to long-on. And that's the 100 partnership
walks across his stumps, and nurdles the ball fine, picked up at fine leg
defended, in the air for a while, but lands safely at mid-on
powerful pull, on the front foot. That's one of his trademark swipes, and midwicket can't intercept that
tucked into the leg side to complete another over

faster, flatter arm ball traps Bell back in the crease ...it was hitting, no doubts there, but was there a sniff of an edge? It matters not a jot because he's on his way ... but he's muttering all the way back to the hutch ...
down the leg and turned into space for the single
swept from leg stump to the man just behind in the deep
pushed through and defended
steps back and cuts through the covers
full and driven back to the bowler on the half volley
checked push into the off side
flicked to leg
a swing, head in the air, a thick edge booms over where slips would be and goes fine enough to beat third man
he misses as he shapes to turn into the leg side, the ball cannons off the pads into the covers
flicked to deep midwicket
the ball passes between bat and pad, there's a noise and everyone goes up. The angry fielders then surround Pietersen who just grins ... water and duck's backs.
full and on leg stump, turned round the corner for a quick single as Pietersen was backing up a long way
again leg-side line, it plops off the pad a  few yards and McCullum fields
one step, two steps, and flicked on the half volley to deep midwicket ... the return hits the join of the drop-in pitch and snorts into Vettori's face
good line, defended
driven past a diving short extra cover, mid-off fields but can't prevent the single

he misses an intended flick to leg, and Rauf gives another lbw ... he was a long way forward but despite that it looked a sound decision. Not that Pietersen would agree, and he stares long and hard at the hapless official as he heads off
pushed into the off side
slightly hurried block with little foot movement
slower ball which he picks, launched back over the bowler's head and into the sightscreen
dropped into the covers but the close cordon in quickly to snuffle out thoughts of a single
prodded to the right of backward point and that allows the run
plays and misses
sweetly flicked off his pads to deep midwicket
squirted to backward point
well forward, pushed into the covers
again a long way forward and McCullum coos encouragement to his captain
punched hard past extra cover, hit with the spin
floated up, watched and dead-batted to point
patted back to old brown eyes who fields
whipped from off stump to deep square leg, a curtailed cry of anguish from the bowler
punched off the back foot , again Mills easily gathers without breaking stride
poked towards extra cover
short and Shah quick to seize on it and thump it to deep midwicket .... there should have been one but a fumble allows them to come back for the second
across and into line to defend
pushed to midwicket
dead batted into the leg side
he skips down the track and pushes wide of the bowler who half collides with the non striker, long-on ambles in
very wide and cut to deep cover
driven to mid-off and both batsmen are quick out of the blocks ...had they not been that might have been tight
solid block form Shah.
wicket-to-wicket, defended on off stump
pushed off the front foot, past the outstretched hand of the bowler, fielded at mid-off
short, and pulled firmly into the deep. So firmly, in fact, that Fulton misfields
back of a length, and pushed into the covers
full length, cramping for room outside off, nudged into the gully region
lovely strike, clipped up and over midwicket. Lots of bottom hand involved, and beat all the fielders
far too much width, and carved out to Fulton in the deep. With two misfields to his name already, England were always going to push him for two
pushed into the covers, a loud shout of "no!"
striding onto the front foot, pushed into the covers
stepped to the pitch and worked through the leg side
driven with a full face, picked up behind the stumps by a sliding mid-off
low full toss, driven hard into the covers, and rebounds for a single
jabbed out to point. Not much width to work with
cut away towards point who fails to pick up cleanly and they coast in for a single
tidy line and length, angling in and shaping away, defended uneasily on off stump
short-arm pull through midwicket
swung out towards deep midwicket, a cry of "catch!" goes up, but lucky for Collingwood he didn't connect properly
run off an open face to third man. England are easing home now. Surely
shimmies down the pitch and driven into space in the covers
tight line and length and met with a dead bat, but it's dead enough to pick up a single
down the track, and Martin turns a length ball into a yorker. Good bowling
clipped firmly in front of a diving short midwicket. Nicely timed into the deep
driven wide of short cover. Another one ticked off
waist-high full toss, and Collingwood swats it away, high and handsome over backward square.
tip and run into the off side, very easy
heaved drive past a diving midwicket, the men in the deep converge but not quickly enough to save the second
he steps to leg and hammers the ball through the covers, a super shot at this stage of the game and you can see the Kiwis deflating with every blow
leg-side full toss, jabbed through midwicket and more air escapes ...
pushed to extra cover, the batsmen hurry, the fielder almost seems to have given up the ghost
steered skillfully down to third man, it was full and he opened the face so perfectly that he almost evaded the man down there
chest-high full toss, dismissively swatted into the crowd beyond square leg
chipped over the bowler, not enough power to make the rope but two more
driven over mid-off, it bounces a foot inside the rope and as the man is in the ring, a safe shot
now you suspect he is taking the whatsit ... another full toss reverse swept to perfection
good yorker well dug out and pushed to long-on
slower ball steered to backward point
firmly pushed to point and ironic cheers for the dot ball
low full toss patted to long-on
driven to extra cover
all very anticlimactic now ... the runs will come .... but not off this ball which point fields
crisp drive to deepish mid-off but again no interest in the single
slashed drive to the left of extra cover and this time Shah takes the run to tie the scores
short, pulled but not timed, but it makes no difference as they take the single to backward square leg that wins the match and puts England back in the series
